<emphasis box="[271,492,1842,1861]" italics="true" pageId="36" pageNumber="321">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Álvarez-Padilla" authorityYear="2007" baseAuthorityName="Simon" baseAuthorityYear="1904" box="[271,488,1842,1861]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetragnathidae" genus="Mollemeta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="36" pageNumber="321" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="edwardsi">Mollemeta edwardsi</taxonomicName>
.
</emphasis>
A, female habitus. B, epigynum ventral view. C, caudal view. D, ventral view cleared. E, dorsal view cleared. F–J, male pedipalp. F, cymbium (bulb dissected). G, expanded. H, dorsal view. I, palpal tibia. J, ventral view. Scale bars 0.2 mm, except in habitus 1 mm.
</paragraph>
